vulnerability.name: USN-5855-2
vulnerability.description: USN-5855-1 fixed a vulnerability in ImageMagick. This update provides the corresponding update for Ubuntu 20.04 LTS, Ubuntu 22.04 LTS, and Ubuntu 22.10.  Original advisory details:   It was discovered that ImageMagick incorrectly handled certain PNG images.  If a user or automated system were tricked into opening a specially crafted  PNG file, an attacker could use this issue to cause ImageMagick to stop  responding, resulting in a denial of service, or possibly obtain the  contents of arbitrary files by including them into images.

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in ImageMagick.
